                    <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="Ethiopian" notBefore="1950">
                         <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                           The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards.
                         </decoNote>
                         <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                           The boards are flush with the bookblock and have shallow external bevels. The grain runs vertically.
                           Both the external and internal surfaces of the boards are rough.
                         </decoNote>
                         <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="SewingStations">2</decoNote>
                         <decoNote xml:id="b4">
                           Chainstitch sewing on two sewing stations (one pair). The sewing is carried out with an untwisted thread.
                           In the centrefold of the first quire, between the sewing stations, the ends of two threads are knotted together resulting
                           in a single thread length, while in the rest of the quires the thread lengths are double. In <ref target="#q5"/> the ends of the thread are left long and not knotted.
                         </decoNote>
                         <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="Spine">
                           The small holes close to the head and tail of the quires are probably what remains of quire tackets.
                         </decoNote>
                         <decoNote xml:id="b6" type="SlipCase">
                           The manuscript is provided with a leather two-piece slip case with a strap. The case consists of two halves that fit together to
                           enclose the manuscript. One half is fitted on the head edge, the other on the tail edge. A twisted leather cord passes through two
                           pockets sewn laterally on each of the two halves. The case presents a blind-tooled decoration with <term key="singleStraightLine">single straight lines</term>
                           and <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term>.
                         </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                 </bindingDesc>

